Perfect — since your environment restricts direct internet access, here’s how to manually use the downloaded GPG key from S3 instead of running the full curl command directly on the VM:

⸻

✅ Step-by-Step Remediation

🟩 1. Download the GPG key from your S3 bucket

Replace with your bucket path:

aws s3 cp s3://your-bucket-name/archive-key.asc /tmp/archive-key.asc


⸻

🟩 2. Convert and store the key in the correct location

gpg --dearmor /tmp/archive-key.asc | sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/kali-archive-keyring.gpg > /dev/null


⸻

🟩 3. Update your Kali source list with trusted key reference

echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/kali-archive-keyring.gpg] http://http.kali.org/kali kali-rolling main contrib non-free non-free-firmware" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list


⸻

🟩 4. Clean and update APT

sudo apt clean
sudo apt update


⸻

Let me know your S3 path if you want help adjusting the script. Once this is done, your GPG signature error should be resolved.
